  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Life Saving WASH Services to Rohingya (Teknaf)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In this 2021 proposed PD, Oxfam will improve access to chlorinated water supply by maintaining 01 existing water distribution system connected to a SWAT (surface water treatment plant), upgrade 50 existing biofil latrines&apos; superstructures (semi -permanent), 20 bathing cubicles, regular Operation &amp; Maintenance (O&amp;M) to meet the needs of women and girls, elderly, and persons with disability. Hygiene Promotion activities will focus on RANAS methodology and CCCPLTH with special emphasis in inclusion of most vulnerable groups Gender, Age &amp; Disability (G, A&amp;D). Oxfam will utilise monitoring as a tool for gender, age, and disability. Oxfam is committed to strengthening accountability to affected populations (AAP). Oxfam staff will be trained and sensitized on Disaster Risk Reduction (DRR), AAP, Prevention of Sexual Exploitation and Abuse (PSEA) and gender mainstreaming.</narrative>
  </description>
